News24 CorrespondentPolokwane &ndash; The matric maths II exam paper appears to have been leaked to pupils in Giyani, Limpopo, from Gauteng, Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga said on Friday.It was sent to one pupil at Giyani High School via social media, according to a preliminary investigation, she told reporters in Polokwane. The exam was written on Monday. The pupil shared it with a study group. Some of its members then shared it with pupils in neighbouring schools.Motshekga acknowledged that the integrity of this year&rsquo;s examination had been compromised.She a criminal case had been opened with the Hawks. Motshekga said she was not sure if crooks trying to make a profit from classified documents were behind the leak.&nbsp;Basic education director general Mathanzima Mweli said it was clear the leak was from outside Limpopo. He said the province had contained the leak.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.